**Always use `uv` for Python package management in this project.**

```bash
# make a new env, install dependencies
uv venv
source .venv/bin/activate
uv pip install -e .

# Install additional packages
uv pip install <package-name>
```

use convenience script:

```bash
source scripts/setup_env.sh
```

install node-specific dependencies (defined in `conf/nodes.yaml`)

```bash
# example for "ook" node
uv pip install .[bot,dev,gen,img,viz] .[gpu]
```